Gospel star Khaya Mthethwa and his wife, former Miss South Africa Ntandoyenkosi Kunene-Mthethwa. JOHANNESBURG - Former Miss South Africa Ntandoyenkosi Mthethwa announced on Tuesday her split from her husband, Idols SA season 8 winner, Khaya Mthethwa. In a statement posted on Instagram Ntando said the split was amicable. "On Sunday we met my in-laws and informed them of our mutual decision for us to amicably file for divorce. READ: Wendy Williams files for divorce from husband Kevin Hunter - report I have also informed my mother and the rest of the Kunene family who was disappointed with the divorce decision but appreciated the fact that I represented them well at the Mthethwa's in the way they raised and expected from me", read the post. The couple, who recently celebrated their second wedding anniversary, welcomed their baby boy Oyinkosi earlier this year in February. "I will have custody of our son but at all times his father shall have unrestricted access so that he can play his fatherly role as we co-parent." A post shared by Ntandoyenkosi Kunene-Mthethwa (@mthethwa_ntando) on Dec 23, 2019 at 10:28pm PST